aws is a cloud provider, they provide us with servers and services that we can use on-demand and scale easily.
amazon powers some of the biggest websites in the world (amazon.com and netflix)
Regions span across the globe(us-east-1, ap-south-1)cluster of data centers, most of the aws services are region-scoped
AZs - each region has many availability zones, each az is one or more discrete data centers with reduntant power, network and connectivity, they're separate from each other, so that they are isolated from disasters, they're connected with high bandwidth, ultra low latency and networking
Data Centers
Edge locations/points of presence(content is delivered to end users with low latency)
AWS global service
IAM
WAF
Route 53
cloudfront(content delivery network)
Most AWS services are region scoped
ec2(iaas)
elastic beanstalk(paas)
lambda(function as a service)
Rekognition(software as a service)

if you want to host an application opt that is geographically closest to you/audience around the globe
aws global infrastracture - https://aws.amazon.com/about-aws/global-infrastructure/regional-product-services/?p=ngi&loc=4&refid=14a4002d-4936-4343-8211-b5a150ca592b gives the services by region